<TITLE> Militants issue death warrant </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 02 (bdnews24.com) -- Chief state counsel Anisul Haque, attorney general Mahbubey Alam and special judge Amar Kumar Roy of Dhaka judge's court received death threats on Wednesday from militant organisations. The threat has been made through a letter sent to the Dhaka Court Reporters' Association by post at about 11am. The letter has asked six questions to be answered by the judge concerning some information on the Bangabandhu murder case and cases filed against the militants. The letter written in English refers its senders as the members of al Qaeda, Lashkar-e-Taiba, Jaish-e-Mohammed, Harkat-ul-Jihad-al-Islami (Huji) and Jamaat-ul-Mujahideen Bangladesh (JMB). " No body could save their lives," the letter said. This is third such death threat after the appeals process of Bangabandhu murder case began. The attorney general previously received a piece of shroud and a three-page letter from 'Jamia Islami al Halhalia Bangladesh' within hours of the final verdict on the Bangabandhu murder case on Nov 19. bd
